Black Widow is a 2021 superhero film, based on the Marvel Comics superhero of the same name. The film is a sequel to Captain America: Civil War and a prequel to Avengers: Infinity War. It is the twenty-fourth film in the Marvel Cinematic Universe, and the fourth installment of Phase Four. The film was released on July 9, 2021 in theaters and on Disney+ with Premier Access.Black Widow is a 2021 superhero film, based on the Marvel Comics superhero of the same name. The film is a sequel to Captain America: Civil War and a prequel to Avengers: Infinity War. It is the twenty-fourth film in the Marvel Cinematic Universe, and the fourth installment of Phase Four. The film was released on July 9, 2021 in theaters and on Disney+ with Premier Access.\nIn Marvel Studios\s action-packed spy thriller Black Widow, Natasha Romanoff, aka Black Widow, confronts the darker parts of her ledger when a dangerous conspiracy with ties to her past arises. Pursued by a force that will stop at nothing to bring her down, Natasha must deal with her history as a spy and the broken relationships left in her wake long before she became an Avenger.
